items.prompt: Show total revenue for last month
items.sql: SELECT SUM(total_amount) FROM orders WHERE status = 'DELIVERED' AND order_date >= date_trunc('month', CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '1 month') AND order_date < date_trunc('month', CURRENT_DATE);

items.prompt: Show attendance summary for current month
items.sql: SELECT e.first_name, e.last_name, COUNT(*) as days_present FROM attendance a JOIN employees e ON a.employee_id = e.id WHERE a.date >= date_trunc('month', CURRENT_DATE) AND a.status = 'PRESENT' GROUP BY e.id, e.first_name, e.last_name ORDER BY days_present DESC;

items.prompt: List top 10 customers by total orders
items.sql: SELECT c.first_name, c.last_name, COUNT(o.id) as order_count FROM customers c JOIN orders o ON c.id = o.customer_id GROUP BY c.id, c.first_name, c.last_name ORDER BY order_count DESC LIMIT 10;
SELECT SUM(base_salary + COALESCE(bonus, 0)) FROM salaries WHERE effective_to IS NULL;

items.prompt: List employees by department with their salaries
items.sql: SELECT d.name as department, e.first_name, e.last_name, s.base_salary FROM employees e JOIN departments d ON e.department_id = d.id JOIN salaries s ON e.id = s.employee_id WHERE e.status = 'ACTIVE' AND s.effective_to IS NULL ORDER BY d.name, e.last_name;
SELECT name, stock_quantity FROM products WHERE stock_quantity IS NOT NULL AND stock_quantity < 10 ORDER BY stock_quantity ASC;
